<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-7386] Streams Scala wrapper should not cache serdes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7386</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;for example, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/streams/streams-scala/src/main/scala/org/apache/kafka/streams/scala/Serdes.scala#L28&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/streams/streams-scala/src/main/scala/org/apache/kafka/streams/scala/Serdes.scala#L28&lt;/a&gt;&#160;invokes Serdes.String() once and caches the result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the implementation of the String serde has a non-empty configure method that is variant in whether it&apos;s used as a key or value serde. So we won&apos;t get correct execution if we create one serde and use it for both keys and values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is simple: change all the `val` declarations in scala.Serdes to `def`. Thanks to the referential transparency for parameterless methods in scala, no user-facing code will break.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
